## Hints for Future Agents
- test_trace_server_bindings.py at this commit == its state at the rebuild
  PR; the unconditional `server.call_processor._dropped_item_count = 0` is
  valid for the OLD requests-era binding too (the attribute exists on both
  master processors: async_batch_processor.py:89, call_batch_processor.py:334)
  and on a fresh fixture it is a no-op reset to an already-0 value.
- The old binding (still shipped by this PR) uses httpx via
  weave.utils.http_requests — that is why the surviving exception arm in
  test_requeue_after_max_retries is httpx.ConnectError; the requests arm
  belonged to the OLD git-pinned stainless SDK generation.
- pytest_ignore_collect could not simply lose its stainless branch: with the
  flag gone the whole hook is dead (no _stainless/_remote files remain), so
  it is deleted, not trimmed.
- uv.lock is intentionally untouched: the removed dep group was commented
  out, markers are pytest config — nothing changes resolution.

